replies.bodyText:
@arhimondr :

Meanwhile we can also try to contribute N-way ZIP partition to open source Spark.

That could be the long-term solution. Another worthwhile investigation next half could be to understand how does SparkSQL implement it without N-way ZIP partition. I also see SparkSQL implements some specialized SparkSQL RDD (unfortunately, in Scala). Thus they don't have this Java-Scala interaction design problem :)

